name: Black Devil (Women's)
description:
Black Devil by Two Arms Inc.

Fine Jersey Ringer T- Bella + Canvas 4.2 oz. 100% ring spun combed cotton.

THE INS, THE OUTS, THE WHAT HAVE YOUS Two Arms Inc. is a ( soon to be husband and wife team ) founded by Mike Tabie and Karen Goheen in 2009. We met 6 years ago in Orlando, FL while working with a local design agency and screen-printing together on nights and weekends. We independently moved to New York but continued to work separately within large and small design agencies. After a year we decided to take the plunge and partner together and start a business with our own vision in mind. There is nothing more satisfying then working with someone you love and trust. We love collaborating and getting our hands dirty. We are specialists of the handmade. We believe in craftsmanship, an attention to detail, and that sweet spot between concept and execution. We started this business because we care about what we do, and we want to work with clients who are passionate about their vision. For more info visit http://twoarmsinc.com/

name: Pattern
description:
Pattern by Kristofer Porter

American Apparel 100% fine ring-spun combed cotton jersey.

A designer and illustrator by day, Kris is also an exhibiting artist, showing in NYC and throughout the U.S. If you’re looking for him, you can probably find him holed up in his Brooklyn apartment, talking to himself at a drawing table and trying desperately to get caught up. Or you can just see some of his work at kristoferporter.com.

name: WTF (Men's)
description:
"WTF" by Jiha Moon

Fine Jersey Ringer T- American Apparel 4.3 oz. 100% ring spun combed cotton.

Jiha Moon (b. 1973 DaeGu, Korea) lives and works in Atlanta, Georgia. In her work Jiha merges the traditional techniques and materials of her native Korea, such as handmade hanji paper, with references to global art and culture. Reflecting her personal experiences of cultural translation and assimilation, Jiha Moon creates kaleidoscopic compositions, layering imagery drawn from various cultures and periods. Visit jihamoon.com for more info.

name: Learn (Camel)
description:
"Learn" by M-Lon

American Apparel 4.3 oz. 100% fine ring-spun combed cotton jersey in camel brown.

AKA Miguel Gonzalez, b. Caracas, Venezuela, 1979. A self-trained artist, M-lon draws from his passion for illustration and fine art to create his paintings and drawings. His art gets to the heart of human desire and interaction within his playful works. In 2012 he migrated from Venezuela to Australia, leaving architecture to focus exclusively on his fine art. His art is a mashup of diciplines and media. Traditional methods - acrylic, charcoal, graphite and ink, - are combined with cutting edge digital art approaches to produce a new, engaging hybrid. Currently he runs “Kayapa Creative Studio” in Sydney. More info at www.m-lon.com

The first in a series of shirts based around good lessons for life, there is more great stuff on the way.

Eco-friendly, water based black ink on heather grey American Apparel Tri-Blend Track Tees. These shirts are so soft you could use it as a pillow case, but we suggest wearing it instead.

Available in Women's and Men's sizes Small through XX-Large.

name: The Eagle Flies on Friday T-Shirts
description:
T. Bone Walker used this phrase in "Call It Stormy Monday," a blues classic covered by the likes of the Allman Brothers, Bobby Bland and Eric Clapton. 
 
It was also a common expression for G.I.'s during WWII to signal it was payday and time for a little R & R.  

This 5 colored screenprint on Indigo and Venetian Gray TriBlend Next Level preshrunk 50% polyester/25% cotton/25% rayon jersey.

Please specify color when ordering
